msgid "Translation:"
msgstr "翻译："

msgid "Mark task progress?"
msgstr "记录任务进度？"

msgid "As a reminder from the previous scenario:"
msgstr "上一场景提示："

msgid "Remove <i>The Inescapable</i> encounter set from the game."
msgstr "从游戏中移除<i>穷途异魔</i> 遭遇组。"

msgid "Also gather <i>The Inescapable</i> encounter set."
msgstr "同时收集<i>穷途异魔</i>遭遇组。"

msgid "In player order, each player may choose 1 [[Item]] asset from the <i>Expedition</i> encounter set to begin in play under their control."
msgstr "按玩家顺序，每位玩家可从<b><i>冒险</i></b>遭遇牌组中选择 1 张 [[物品]] 卡牌，在游戏开始时置于自己控制下。"

msgid "In player order, each player may choose 1 earned [[Artifact]] asset or 1 [[Item]] asset from the <i>Expedition</i> encounter set to begin in play under their control."
msgstr "按照玩家回合顺序，每位玩家可从<i>冒险</i> 遭遇牌组中选择 1 件已获得的[[神器]]卡牌或 1 件[[道具]]卡牌，将其置入己方操控的游戏区域。"

msgid "Investigators may acquire certain [[Artifact]] story assets also referred to as simply \"artifacts\" through the course of <i>The Drowned City</i> campaign. Artifacts function like any other asset, except for the following:"
msgstr "调查员在<i>《淹灭之城》</i>剧本的进程中会获取特定的[[神器]]剧情支援（也简称为“神器”）。神器与其他支援功能相仿，但有以下例外："

msgid "Artifacts are never added to investigator decks. After resolution of a scenario, return any artifacts in play to the box."
msgstr "神器绝不会加入调查员的牌库。在冒险结局之后，将场上的所有神器放回游戏盒中。"

msgid "When setting up a scenario, investigators may be instructed to begin play with an earned [[Artifact]] story asset. Only artifacts that have been checked off in the \"Artifacts Earned\" section of the Campaign Log may be chosen during this process."
msgstr "在设置冒险时，调查员可能会受到指示，以取得的[[神器]]剧情支援在场上的情况下开始游戏。在这一过程期间，只有在剧本日志的“取得的神器”部分打了勾的[[神器]]，才可以被选择。"

msgid "Artifacts have a unique card back, have no cost, cannot leave play, and cannot be chosen to be discarded via scenario effects."
msgstr "神器有独特的牌背，没有费用，不能离场，也不能因冒险效果被选择弃掉。"

msgid "Some artifacts contain alien glyphs <i>(see</i> <b>Alien Glyphs</b> <i>below)</i>. Any text below these glyphs is considered to be blank unless investigators have translated each alien glyph on the artifact."
msgstr "有些神器带有异星字符<i>（见下文</i><b>异星字符</b><i>部分）</i>。这些字符下面的所有文本均视为空白，除非调查员已经翻译了该神器上的每个异星字符。。"

msgid "If any investigator in control of an artifact is defeated, <b>give control of it to the nearest surviving investigator</b> instead of removing it from the game."
msgstr "如果有任意控制了神器的调查员被击败，不将其神器从游戏中移除，而是改为<b>由最近的幸存调查员控制该神器</b>。"

msgid "Throughout the campaign, investigators may be directed to translate a glyph on the second page of the Campaign Log. In order to do so, write the translated text in the space directly beneath that glyph, as directed by the game."
msgstr "在这个剧本中，调查员可能会受到指示，要翻译剧本日志第二页的字符。要翻译字符，就按照游戏的指示，将译文直接写在对应字符下面的空白处。"

msgid "A glyph's meaning has no inherent game effect."
msgstr "字符的含义本身没有游戏效果。"

msgid "Some artifacts contain alien glyphs <i>(see</i> <b>Artifacts</b> <i>above)</i>. Any text below these glyphs is considered to be blank unless investigators have translated each alien glyph on the artifact."
msgstr "有些神器带有异星字符<i>（见上文</i><b>神器</b><i>部分）</i>。这些字符下面的所有文本均视为空白，除非调查员已经翻译了该神器上的每个异星字符。"

msgid "Most scenarios in <i>The Drowned City</i> campaign will instruct players to set [[Glyph]] cards aside, out of play. Most [[Glyph]] cards are double-sided story cards with another encounter cardtype on their front. For the best experience, do not read their story card sides unless prompted by the game!"
msgstr "<i>《淹灭之城》</i>剧本的大多数冒险都会指示玩家将[[字符]]卡牌放在一边，位于场外。大多数[[字符]]卡牌都是双面的剧情卡牌，正面则是某种遭遇卡牌。为了最佳的游戏体验，除非游戏要求，否则不要阅读其剧情卡牌的一面!"

msgid "For the sake of your sanity, do not stare at any alien glyph for longer than 5 minutes at a time."
msgstr "为了你的神智健康，每次凝视异星字符不要超过5分钟。"

msgid "Some enemies in this campaign have the relentless keyword. During the enemy phase (after framework step 3.3), each enemy with the relentless keyword that has attacked this phase (even if that attack was canceled) readies and attacks the investigator(s) it is engaged with a second time."
msgstr "这个剧本中部分敌人带有“无情”关键词。在敌军阶段期间（流程步骤3.3后），每个本阶段已经攻击过的敌人（即便其攻击被取消），若带有无情关键词，会重整并再次攻击与其交战的调查员。"

msgid ""
"As an additional cost for a card with the seal keyword to enter play, its controller must search the chaos bag for the specified chaos token and place it on top of the card, thereby sealing the token. If there is a choice of which token to seal, the card's controller chooses. If the specified token is not in the chaos bag, the card cannot enter play."
"A sealed chaos token is not considered to be in the chaos bag, and therefore cannot be revealed from the chaos bag as part of a skill test or ability."
"When a chaos token is \"released,\" it is returned to the chaos bag and is no longer considered sealed. <b>If a card with one or more chaos tokens sealed on it leaves play for any reason, any chaos tokens sealed on it are immediately released</b>."
"Some cards (with or without the seal keyword) may also have abilities that seal one or more chaos tokens as part of their effect. This is done following the same process as above: searching the chaos bag for the specified token, removing it from the chaos bag, and placing it on the card. If the specified token is not in the chaos bag, the effect fails."
msgstr ""
"带有封印关键词的卡牌入场时有额外费用，控制该卡牌的玩家必须查找混乱袋，找出指定的混乱标记并放到该卡牌上，以此来封印这个标记。如果该卡牌显示选择一个标记进行封印，则由控制该卡牌的玩家来选择。如果指定的标记不在混乱袋中，则该卡牌不能入场。"
"被封印的混乱标记视为不在混乱袋中，因此在技能检定或结算能力时无法从混乱袋中揭示该标记。"
"在“释放”一个混乱标记时，将该标记放回混乱袋，且该标记不再视为被封印。<b>如果卡牌上封印有混乱标记，该卡牌因任何原因而离场时，立即释放该卡牌上所有的混乱标记。</b>"
"部分卡牌（不论是否带有封印关键词）的能力效果可能也能够封印混乱标记。在这种情况下，同样按照上述过程进行：查找混乱袋，找出特定的标记，将该标记从混乱袋中移除并放到该卡牌上。如果指定的标记不在混乱袋中，则该效果不生效。"

msgid "Tasks in the Drowned City Campaign"
msgstr "淹灭之城剧本的任务"

msgid "Each investigator must select a different \"Task\" to complete over the course of The Drowned City campaign. Tasks represent the investigators' obligations and their reasons for becoming involved with Tillinghast and his shady dealings."
msgstr "在《淹灭之城》剧本中，每位调查员都必须选择完成一个不同的“任务”。任务代表了调查员的重担，以及调查员为什么会认识蒂林哈斯特并牵涉进他可疑的交易。"

msgid "Each investigator must choose a different Task."
msgstr "每位调查员必须选择一个不同的任务。"

msgid "Each Task is recommended for a specific kind of investigator. However, an investigator may choose any Task, even if it is not recommended. <i>(It is up to you to justify how your investigator got into this mess in the first place!)</i>"
msgstr "每个任务都有特定推荐的一批调查员。不过，调查员可以选择任何任务，即使该任务并不推荐。<i>（毕竟，还是由你决定你的调查员究竟是怎么卷入这场麻烦的!）</i>"

msgid "Each Task corresponds to a double-sided [[Task]] card, which can be found in the <i>Tasks</i> encounter set."
msgstr "每个任务对应一张双面的[[任务]]卡牌，可以在<i>任务</i>遭遇组中找到。"

msgid "Investigators should attempt to complete objectives on their [[Task]] card once per scenario over the course of a campaign. Each investigator will also be prompted to resolve story text during setup and/or resolution of a scenario. <i>(Be aware that some outcomes may impact setup.)</i>"
msgstr "在剧本进程中，调查员应该在每场冒险中，都努力完成其[[任务]]卡牌上的目标一次。在一场冒险的设置和/或结局期间，每位调查员也会收到指示，结算其剧情文本。<i>（注意有的结果可能会影响设置。）</i>"

msgid "When instructed to mark or erase 1 or more progress in your Campaign Log, check or uncheck that many boxes under your Task."
msgstr "在收到指示要在剧本日志上记录或擦去进展时，在你的任务底下勾选或取消勾选对应数量的方框。"

msgid "Completing Task objectives will earn experience and /or rewards later in the campaign. The more times an investigator completes their Task, the better. For a more positive outcome, do not ignore your Task!"
msgstr "完成任务的目标会取得经验值，抑或/以及在剧本中随后获得奖励。调查员完成任务的次数越多越好。为了这些好处，可别忽略你的任务!"

msgid "During this scenario, locations are arranged in a set pattern of 5 levels."
msgstr "本场冒险期间，地点排列成5个不同深度的模式。"

msgid "The position of each location has its own level from 1-5, beginning at Western Wall at level 1 and descending to the bottommost locations at level 5."
msgstr "每个地点的位置都有各自的深度，从1至5，从西墙开始为深度1，一路往下，最底下的地点为深度5。"

msgid "Any card effects that refer to a location's level refer to its numbered row, as shown in the location placement diagram."
msgstr "任何涉及地点深度的卡牌效果，指的就是地点在第几行，如右侧的地点摆放示意图所示。"

msgid "<b>During this scenario, each location is connected to each location in the row above it and the row below it. Locations in the same row are not connected to one another.</b>"
msgstr "<b>本场冒险期间，每个地点都与其上一行及下一行的每个地点相互连接。同一行的地点彼此之间不连接。</b>"

msgid "The position of each location has its own level from 1-5, beginning at Obsidian Foundations at level 1 and ascending to the topmost locations at level 5."
msgstr "每个地点的位置都有各自的深度，从1至5，从黑曜石基层开始为深度1，一路往上，最顶上的地点为深度5。"
